originalText.text: This program has been incredible for my daughter. She actually enjoys waking up on Saturdays to spend 3 hours engaging with classmates and learning. It's amazing how she is even more excited in the summer to spend a full day with her friends and teacher who makes the day pleasant and enjoyable. I love how the program grows with my daughter and how it feels like a community with the parents who attend the workshops. I recommed this program to anyone who has a child struggling with reading and who may not be as social. By the time it hits a month you will see a shift in their performance and academics.

originalText.text: The GO Project is made to help young children excel in their education. The only thing I find they are good for is putting children on waiting list and when parents go to try see if their children are actually being acknowledged they are no help because they just take take your child's name and who knows if they look it up. It's another excuse and another waiting list. Why advertise the services they supposedly have to offer if they are not up to willing to provide them to the children being that they are all on waiting list and who knows when and if they will ever be accepted....
